  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustaining a Continuum of Care for  Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn, Child and Adolescent Health (RMNCH +A) services in Humanitarian Settings</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Action Health Incorporated (AHI) seeks to support life-saving assistance and alleviate suffering through an integrated and coordinated humanitarian response focused on providing Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn, Child and Adolescent Health (RMNCH +A) services in the hard-to-reach areas of Borno State, Nigeria, which are the most affected states by the insurgency group, Boko Haram. This project will focus on providing urgent lifesaving services to three Local Government Areas namely Gwoza, Bama,Kala Balge (Borno State) which are severely affected by the insurgence with most health facilities completely destroyed and several persons displaced, while many are unaccounted for. At the end of the project cycle, this project design aims to reduce maternal Mortality, Infant/child mortality and morbidity in the four Hotspot LGAs with urgent need of live saving interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
